orating methods from disciplines such as art history and women’s and cinema studies and considers a variety of images including promotional posters, lobby pictures, and playbills of theatrical and cinematic adaptations of the book. Using a visual studies approach, The Image of Celestina ultimately illuminates the culture of Celestina, a mythical figure, who surpasses the literary text in which she originated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCelestina (Fictitious character) in art. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aBotero.  aCelestina.  aDon Quixote.  aGoya.  aMurillo.  aPicasso.  aSpanish literature.  abawd.  abook history.  abook illustrations.  adepictions of prostitution in art.  afamous Spanish novels.  aprocuress.  aprostitute.  asex work.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079736740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754982440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487549824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487549824/original  a978-3-11-079736-7  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles